<section xml:id="derivatives-integrals-review">
	<title>Review -- Derivatives and Integrals</title>
	<p>
		The final approach to accumulating interest we will discuss generalizes all of the others that we have studied -- the force of interest.  Using this concept requires some basic differentiation and integration, which we will practice in this activity. To review some basic derivative and integral rules, go to <xref ref="appendix-differentiation-integration"/>.
	</p>
	<activity xml:id="derivatives">
		<introduction>
			<p> 
				Find the derivatives of the following functions.
			</p>
		</introduction>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>f(t) = \ln(1+\iota t)</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>f(t) = e^{rt}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>f(t) = \frac{\iota}{1+\iota t}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>f(t) = t \sqrt{(1+t)^2-1}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>f(t) = \frac{t}{\sqrt{(1+t)^2-1}}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>f(x) = x^x</m>
			</p>
		</task>
	</activity>
	<activity xml:id="integration-practice">
		<introduction>
			<p> 
				Calculate the following definite integrals.
			</p>
		</introduction>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>\displaystyle{\int_0^5 r dt}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>\displaystyle{\int_0^t r dr}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>\displaystyle{\int_3^6 \frac{t^2}{50} dt}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>\displaystyle{\int_0^4 \frac{\iota}{1+\iota t} dt}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>\displaystyle{\int_5^6 \frac{2t}{1+t^2} dt}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
		<task>
			<p> 
				<m>\displaystyle{\int_0^t  \frac{r^2}{1+r^3} dr}</m>
			</p>
		</task>
	</activity>
	<activity xml:id="differentiation-integration-reflection">
		<statement>
			<p> 
				Which differentiation and integration skills do you need additional practice with?
			</p>
		</statement>
	</activity>
</section>